IMP System – User Guide (Department User)

Inventory Maintenance Form  ·  Material Requisition Slip  ·  Purchase Advice  ·  WebFocus Solutions, Inc.  ·  February 2026

About this guide: This guide covers everything a Department User needs to operate the IMP System — including signing in, managing your account, and handling Material Requisition Slips (MRS).
CH 1

Getting Started

What is the IMP System?

The IMP (Inventory Maintenance Form – Material Requisition Slip – Purchase Advice) System is a fully electronic platform for Philsaga Mining Corporation. It handles stock viewing, updating stock descriptions, requesting stocks, purchasing stocks, and system maintenance. Its main objective is to ensure timely service to requesters and enhance the MCD's key performance indicators (KPIs).

Introduction – IMP System Overview

How do I sign in?

  1. Go to the Admin Portal web address.
  2. Enter your Email and Password.
  3. Click the Login button to complete the process.

Sign-In – Admin Sign-in Page

How do I reset my password if I forgot it?

  1. Go to the Admin Portal Sign-in page and click Forgot Password.
  2. Enter your email address on the Forgot Password page.
  3. Click Submit. A password reset link will be sent to your email.
  4. Open the Reset Password Notification email and click the Reset Password link.
  5. Enter your new password (minimum 8 characters) and re-enter it to confirm.
  6. Click Reset Password to complete.

Reset Password – Forgot Password flow

Reset Password – Email notification & Reset Password page

How do I change my password while logged in?

  1. Log in to the Admin Portal. The Dashboard page will appear.
  2. Click your Profile Icon at the top right.
  3. Choose Manage Account.
  4. On the My Profile screen, click the Change Password link.
  5. Enter your new password in the New Password field.
  6. Re-enter it in the Re-Type New Password field.
  7. Click Update to finalize.

Change Password – My Account & Change Password screen

Note: Changing your password will log you out automatically. You will need to re-login with the new password.

How do I sign out?

  1. Click the Profile Icon at the top right of the screen.
  2. Click Sign Out to log out of the system.

Sign Out

CH 2

Home

What is the Home page?

The Home page is the landing page for all IMP System users. From here you can browse the full product catalog, search for specific items, or filter by category to find products available for requisition.

Home – Product Catalog

How do I view the product catalog?

  1. Go to the Home option in the left sidebar.
  2. Click the View Catalogue button to see all listed products.
  3. Use the Search bar to find specific products by name, description, or item code.
  4. Use Browse by Category to filter products by category.

Product Catalogue – Search & Browse by Category

CH 3

Material Requisition Slip (MRS)

What is a Material Requisition Slip (MRS)?

The Material Requisition Slip (MRS) is a formal internal document used to request the issuance or purchase of materials needed for operations, production, maintenance, or projects inside Philsaga Mining Corporation. It authorizes the store, warehouse, or purchasing department to release specific items and serves as an official audit and cost-allocation record.

Key information included in an MRS: MRS number, date of request, department or project name, description of materials, quantity required, purpose or reason for request, and cost code.

Available MRS functions: Create, Edit, View, Submit, Cancel, and Export.

How do I create an MRS?

  1. Go to the MRS option in the left sidebar.
  2. Click Add New MRS to start.
  3. Review the Cart screen for any previously added products.
  4. Click Add More Product to browse and add items.
  5. Hover over a product and click the Cart icon to add it. Use the search bar to find specific items.
  6. Click the Cart button to return to the cart and review your selection.
  7. Click Proceed to Checkout.
  8. Fill in all required fields (Priority, Date Needed, Code Type, Cost Code, Department, Section, Purpose per item, etc.) and attach any files.
  9. Click Place Request to submit.
  10. Your request number will be shown on the confirmation screen.

Create MRS – MRS Dashboard

Create MRS – Review and Place Request form

Create MRS – Request confirmation with MRS number

Note: After saving, the MRS is not yet submitted to MCD. You must submit it to your head for approval.

How do I edit an MRS?

  1. Go to the MRS option in the left sidebar.
  2. Use the Search bar or Pagination to locate the MRS you want to edit.
  3. Click the Edit icon (pencil icon) in the Options column.
  4. Make all necessary changes.
  5. Click Save to save your changes.

Edit MRS – Options icons

How do I view an MRS?

  1. Go to the MRS option in the left sidebar.
  2. Use the Search bar or Pagination to find the MRS.
  3. Click the View icon (eye icon) in the Options column.
  4. A pop-up window will display the full MRS details including items, quantities, approvers, and status.

View MRS – MRS detail pop-up

How do I submit an MRS to the Workflow System (WFS)?

  1. Go to the MRS option in the left sidebar.
  2. Use Search or Pagination to find the saved MRS.
  3. Click the Submit icon (upload arrow icon) in the Options column.

Submit MRS – Submit icon in Options

Important: There is NO confirmation screen when submitting. Once submitted, the MRS status changes to "Posted" and can no longer be edited.

How do I cancel an MRS?

  1. Go to the MRS option in the left sidebar.
  2. Use Search or Pagination to find the MRS.
  3. Click the Cancel icon (circle with slash icon) in the Options column.
  4. A confirmation pop-up will appear. Click Continue to confirm the cancellation.

Cancel MRS – Confirmation pop-up

How do I export the MRS list to Excel?

  1. Go to the MRS option in the left sidebar.
  2. Click the Export as Excel button at the top of the MRS dashboard.
  3. The full MRS list will be downloaded as an Excel file.

Export MRS – Export as Excel button

Export MRS – Sample Excel output
